transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi. Thank you so much for calling Viagra. My name is Jessie. Can I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Hi. This is Roger Hofstetter.

Speaker 1: Hofstetter. Great. Mr. Hofstetter, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: I'm calling to cancel my account, please.

Speaker 1: Oh, no. And are you canceling this because the pills, you know, aren't working that well for you?

Speaker 2: Or is it just because of the frequency? Because it's like every two months, which is kind of a lot.

Speaker 1: No, it's a change in health.

Speaker 2: Oh, gotcha. Oh, I'm so sorry. All right.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Yeah. The one that was charged on the 25th, that one's already shipped out. I'll note that as your last.

Speaker 1: But I'm just going to throw this out there in case you want to do this, if there is a change in health,

Speaker 2: because your prescription is still active and you still have refills.

Speaker 1: I can pause everything for either four or six months.

Speaker 2: And that just puts everything on pause. You don't get anything in the mail.

Speaker 1: No surprises, no anything like that.

Speaker 2: So that way, if you are still, you know, if things change and you still want to place orders down the line,

Speaker 1: your prescription is still active. Would you like me to do that?

Speaker 2: No. I wish it was possible, but no. Sorry.

Speaker 1: Okay. No problem. Just thought I'd ask.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Appreciate it.

Speaker 2: All right. No problem. Okay.

Speaker 1: So it's been canceled, and the one that was charged on the 25th is noted as your last. Okay?

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: All right. Have a great day. Bye-bye.
